public class JsCSS2Properties
extends DOM2CSS.CSS2Properties.Prototype

An opaque class representing JavaScript client-side objects of the global JsClient.CSS2Properties class.

An object of this class represents a set of CSS style attributes and their values. It defines one JavaScript property for each CSS attribute defined by the CSS2 specification. The JsHTMLElement.style property of a JsHTMLElement object is a read/write object of this opaque class, as is the JsCSSRule.style JsWindow.getComputedStyle(JsHTMLElement, String), however, is an object of this class whose properties are read-only.

In addition to the cssText property, an object of this class also has a property corresponding to each CSS attribute that the browser supports. These property names correspond closely to the CSS attribute names, with minor changes required to avoid syntax errors in JavaScript. Multi-word attributes that contain hyphens, such as "font-family", are written without hyphens in JavaScript, and each word after the first is capitalized: fontFamily. Also, the "float" attribute conflicts with the reserved word float, so it translates to the property cssFloat.

Note that some browsers do not support all CSS attributes and may not implement all of the listed properties. All of the properties are strings. Setting any of these properties may throw the same exceptions as setting the cssText property.

cssText

public static final Value.String.Member cssText

An opaque static field defining a member that is named by the field name without a qualifying member and to access the property of the name on an object.

The textual representation of a set of style attributes and their values. The text is formated as in a CSS stylesheet, minus the element selector and the curly braces that surround the attributes and values. Setting this property to an illegal value throws a JsDOMException with the JsDOMException.code property of the value JsDOMException.SYNTAX_ERR. Attempting to set this property when the current object is read-only throws a JsDOMException exception with the JsDOMException.code property of the value JsDOMException.NO_MODIFICATION_ALLOWED_ERR.
